Amount given will be dependent on individual families' assessed need, for one-off emergency assistance for specific expenditure, staggered between a minimum and maximum amount.

Provision of Winter Cash Assistance (280 JD) to the identified most vulnerable Syrian Refugees and their households to cover  their basic needs. The Seasonal assistance (Winter) Beneficiaries will be provided with additional Regular Cash Assistance during the 3 months following the provision of the Winter assistance (3*130 JD)

Information related to Women, Men, Boys and Girls individuals are based on percentages estimations provided by the UNHCR. Actual information will be available further on and data will be updated accordingly.

Indicator: Boys - Other affected Population - # of individuals assisted - Unconditional
comments:
Regular short-term three-month cash assistance of an average of 150JOD per family per month to most-vulnerable Syrian and Jordanian households to assist with the meeting of essential needs.

Cash programming vulnerability criteria, standards, and coverage will continue to be coordinated with other members of the Cash Working Group. Amount given per month will be dependent on individual families' assessed need, staggered between a minimum and maximum amount.

Indicator: Syrian Men in Urban - # of individuals assisted - Unconditional
comments:
Regular short-term three-month cash assistance of an average of 150JOD per family per month to most-vulnerable Syrian and Jordanian households to assist with the meeting of essential needs.

Cash programming vulnerability criteria, standards, and coverage will continue to be coordinated with other members of the Cash Working Group. Amount given per month will be dependent on individual families' assessed need, staggered between a minimum and maximum amount.

comments:
Emergency one-off cash assistance of an average value of 130JOD most-vulnerable Syrian refugee and Jordanian households.

Cash assistance, vulnerability criteria, standards, and coverage has been coordinated with other members of the Cash Working Group. Indicator: Syrian Boys in Urban - # of individuals assisted - Unconditional
comments:
Provision of Regular Cash Assistance during 3 months (3*130 JD). For 70% of the beneficiaries the regular cash assistance will sum to the provision of the Winter assistance (280 JD) to the identified most vulnerable Syrian Refugees and their households to cover their basic needs. 

Information related to Women, Men, Boys and Girls individuals are based on percentages estimations provided by the UNHCR in a temporary basis. Actual information will be available further on and data will be updated accordingly.
